Package branchandbound

Class BranchAndBound

java.lang.Object
branchandbound.BranchAndBound
Direct Known Subclasses:
Schedule
public class BranchAndBound extends Object
This class solves a branch and bound problem and represents a branch and bound with nodes.
Author:
Florian Korn, Andre Konersmann

  • Method Details

    • setNodes

      public void setNodes(Preemption job, Preemption parentJob, Preemption parentParentJob)
      This method manages the nodes for a branch and bound tree. First it copies the old nodes and then adds the new node. The parent of the parent job is needed to identify the previous node in a backward search when starting at a random node in the tree.
      Parameters:
      job - which represents a node in a tree structure of a branch and bound problem
      parentJob - is the job with a higher hierarchy
      parentParentJob - is the parent of the parent job

    • rootProblem

      public void rootProblem(Preemption[] sequence)
      This method initiates the root problem. It sets a empty node and caluclates the maximum lateness of it. Afterwards the first depth of the tree is set and calculated
      Parameters:
      sequence - of all jobs

    • getNodeJobs

      public Preemption[] getNodeJobs(Node node)
      This method searches all jobs in a given branch and bound tree structure until the given node.
      Parameters:
      node - is the pointer where we are in the tree structure
      Returns:
      sequence with jobs (including the current node and their parents)

    • sortJobs

      public Preemption[] sortJobs(Preemption[] sequence)
      This method sorts an array that the order is switched backwards (last entry is first entry ...)
      Parameters:
      sequence - to sort in switched order
      Returns:
      switched order sequence

    • calcNodeMaxLateness

      public void calcNodeMaxLateness(Preemption job, Preemption parentJob, Preemption parentParentJob, Preemption[] sequence)
      This method sets a node and calculates the node max lateness
      Parameters:
      job - is the node
      parentJob - is the job in a higher hierarchy than the job
      parentParentJob - is the parent of the parent job (in a higher higher hierarchy)
      sequence - of all available jobs

    • branching

      public boolean branching(Preemption[] sequence)
      This method compares the upper bound and establishes a new depth for the node with most potential
      Parameters:
      sequence - of all jobs
      Returns:
      true if it has preemption, otherwise false

    • buildDepth

      public boolean buildDepth(Preemption[] sequence, Node job)
      This method establishes another depth level into the branch and bound tree
      Parameters:
      sequence - of all jobs
      job - that is set in the new node
      Returns:
      true if preemption is used, false if not

    • checkOptimalSolution

      public boolean checkOptimalSolution(Preemption[] sequence)
      This method checks if perhaps there is a better solution than our optimal solution
      Parameters:
      sequence - of all jobs
      Returns:
      true if there is a better solution, false if not
